<h1>Soft Chocolate Chip Cookies</h1>

<p style="text-align:center;">
A simple and delicious recipe for soft homemade chocolate chip cookies.
Great for snacks, parties, or sharing with family.
</p>

<h2>Ingredients Needed</h2>

<ul>
<li>1 cup softened butter</li>
<li>3/4 cup white sugar</li>
<li>3/4 cup brown sugar</li>
<li>2 eggs</li>
<li>2 teaspoons vanilla extract</li>
<li>2 1/4 cups all-purpose flour</li>
<li>1 teaspoon baking soda</li>
<li>1 teaspoon salt</li>
<li>2 cups chocolate chips</li>
</ul>

<h2>Steps to Follow</h2>

<ol>
<li>Heat the oven to 190°C.</li>
<li>Mix the butter, white sugar, and brown sugar until smooth.</li>
<li>Add the eggs one by one, then mix in the vanilla.</li>
<li>In another bowl, combine flour, baking soda, and salt.</li>
<li>Slowly mix the dry ingredients into the wet mixture.</li>
<li>Add the chocolate chips and mix well.</li>
<li>Place spoonfuls of dough onto a baking tray.</li>
<li>Bake for about 10 minutes or until golden brown.</li>
<li>Let the cookies cool before serving.</li>
</ol>

